results.name: Number of commutative rings with 1 containing n elements.
comment: Answer: yes! See the Eric M. Rains link for a proof for the result for all unital rings; restricting to commutative rings does not affect the essence of the proof. - _Jianing Song_, Feb 02 2020
link: C. Noebauer, Home page [Archived copy as of 2008 from web.archive.org]
Eric M. Rains, The number of unital rings with n elements is a multiplicative function of n.
